titles.title: To provide for the liquidation or reliquidation of certain entries of garlic.

action.text: Referred to the House Committee on Ways and Means.
Referred to the Subcommittee on Trade.

committee.name: House Committee on Ways and Means

bill.summary: 3/22/2001--Introduced. Directs the U.S. Customs Service to liquidate or reliquidate as free from duty certain entries of garlic, and refund any duties paid on them.
